  "title": "Counsellor (Genetic, Clinic)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><p><p><ul><li>The Genetic Counsellor is responsible for supporting patients and their families by offering guidance and education on genetic disorders and hereditary health risks.</li><li>Key duties involve reviewing personal and family health histories, determining suitability for genetic testing, and explaining test outcomes.</li><li>The role also includes working closely with healthcare professionals to develop individualized care strategies and to help patients understand their choices and make informed healthcare decisions.</li></ul></p></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p><p><ul><li>Master's degree in Genetic Counseling or any related fields.</li><li>Experience in medical or clinical genetics, either through academic study or practical application.</li><li>Excellent communication and presentation skills</li></ul></p></p><p>Interested applicants for the above advertised position(s), please kindly email an updated copy of your resume to: <strong>gs1@talenttradersg.com;</strong></p><p><br /></p><p>EA License No.: 13C6305</p><p>Registration No.: R23117856 CHOE KIN MUN</p><p><br /></p><p>For candidate who applied for the advertised position is deemed to have consented to us that we may collect, use or disclose your personal information for purpose in connection with the services provided by us.</p>",
